# Memory Bank sync

Curated context lives under `docs/memory/`. Roles and layering: [docs/README.md](../../docs/README.md). Full policy also in the **Memory Bank** section of [AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md).

## When to update

After **any substantive change**—feature, bug fix, refactor, config, tooling, or documentation that affects how the repo is built, run, or understood—**before finishing the task**, bring the memory bank up to date so the next session is not stale.

**Usually not required:** typo-only edits, comment-only tweaks, one-line formatting with no behavioral or doc meaning.

## How

Use the **memory-bank-update** skill (`.cursor/skills/memory-bank-update/SKILL.md`) for the full update workflow, file routing, and safety rules.

## How to verify

1. **Check `docs/memory/activeContext.md`** — must reflect the current session's changes, focus area, and next steps
2. **Check `docs/memory/progress.md`** — any new feature, fix, or WIP should be listed with accurate status
3. **Review timestamps** — updated memory files should have recent modification dates (`git diff --stat docs/memory/`)
4. **Cross-check with code changes** — every substantive code change (feature, fix, refactor, config) must have a corresponding memory bank entry
5. **No stale info** — read through updated files and confirm nothing contradicts the current state of the codebase
